This paper is about generating C code for fast inference of convolutional neural networks on resource-constrained systems. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with neural networks and their deployment. The second likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as convolutional neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks. The third likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper mentions the use of the system in robotics applications. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.EM (Embedded Systems), as the paper deals with resource-constrained systems. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper discusses the optimization of the code generation for the target platform.
